    "Protein engineering Topological Deep Learning is revolutionizing the way scientists approach the vast mutational space of proteins.",
    "It is particularly transformative when combined with existing protein structure prediction tools like AlphaFold2, enabling more precise and powerful structure-based strategies in protein engineering.",
    "Topological Deep Learning in this field is not just enhancing the speed and accuracy of protein design and analysis, but also opening new pathways for advancements in drug discovery, antibody development, and beyond (Qiu and Wei 2023a; Chen et al. 2022; Qiu and Wei 2023b).",
    "Smart manufacturing TDA with deep learning enables enhanced detection of patterns and anomalies in manufacturing processes.",
    "This integration not only improves predictive maintenance but also optimizes production efficiency and quality control, paving the way for more intelligent and responsive manufacturing systems (Ko and Koo 2023; Sarpietro et al. 2022; Uray et al. 2023)."
